itemcol.Paragraphs: KML m Is the distance from the keel to the longitudinal metacenter of the rig KMT m Is the distance from the keel to the transverse metacenter of the rig. GML m Is the longitudinal metacentric height of the rig before free surface correction GMT m Is the transverse metacentric height of the rig before free surface correction FSL m Is the longitudinal free surface correction for slack tanks FST
start signal until LSL gives signal back to input that necessary level of water has been reached
